parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Takata Airbag Recall Parts Distribution Disconnect
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inability to obtain the necessary parts for the Takata airbag recall repair can lead to a delay in fixing the potentially faulty airbag system, which can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: notification of recall but no available parts for repair

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, as the vehicle may surge forward or accelerate unexpectedly, making it difficult for the driver to maintain control.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and spontaneously without the driver's input
the vehicle surges forward or accelerates unexpectedly
the brakes are ineffective in stopping the vehicle
the vehicle continues to accelerate even when the driver applies the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Complete brake failure can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities, as the vehicle may not be able to stop in time or at all.
symptoms: brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake warning lights illuminate on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive wear on brake pads can lead to reduced braking performance, increased stopping distances, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Squealing or grinding noises when applying the brakes
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake warning lights illuminate on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive wear on tires can lead to reduced traction, increased risk of tire blowouts, and increased risk of accidents.
Malfunctions in the infotainment system can cause distractions while driving, leading to increased risk of accidents.
